FBIS3-3895 "drchi057_v_94019" FBIS-CHI-94-057 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Mar 1994 TAIWAN Net Capital Outflow Registers Six-Year Low OW2203083994 Taipei CNA in English 0715 GMT 22 Mar 94 OW2203083994 Taipei CNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [By Danielle Yang] [Text] Taipei, March 22 (CNA) -- Taiwan's net capital outflow dropped to a six-year low of US$4.049 billion in 1993, according to statistics released by the Central Bank of China (CBC) Tuesday [22 March]. In 1992, net capital outflow was US$8.556 billion, more than double the 1993 figure, a CBC official noted. In 1987, net capital outflow was US$2.386 billion. In 1990, the figure hit a six-year high of US$10.552 billion, the statistics showed. CBC attributed the sharp decrease in net capital outflow to the inward remittance of cash by foreign institutional investors and a decrease in outward investment by local investors.
